                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>public eye. The Asmonean will not admit, an antidote to its<lb/>\n                                        own poison, malignant misconstruction might ascribe any\n                                        article<lb/> in the Occident to the pen or dictation of its\n                                        Editor, &amp; thought<lb/> of offering an article to the\n                                        “Sunday Times” the Editor of which<lb/> has always professed\n                                        the most friendly interest for your<lb/> welfare, &amp;\n                                        respect for your character, But will he give currency<lb/>\n                                        to what may tend to the disparagement &amp; infamy of a\n                                        paper<lb/> of which his Son is associate Editor, but I see\n                                        no remedy<lb/> but to test him. I shall prepare an article\n                                        for the Times—<lb/> and <persName>Mr Schoal</persName> has\n                                        promised to furnish one for the Occident,<lb/> with regard\n                                        to <persName>Mr Peynados</persName> letter I called\n                                        yestermorning at<lb/> the Sanctum of the Asmn. But found\n                                        only the junior Editor to<lb/> whom in absence of his Senior\n                                        I showed it, he thought it had been copied<lb/> from the\n                                        Presbyterian, but on referring to the file found that the\n                                        Editor<lb/> in a note referred to a private source from\n                                        which he had derived it.<lb/> I left it with him to be\n                                        handed <persName>Mr. S.</persName> with a promise that he\n                                        should<lb/> by letter give the required explanation to\n                                                  <persName>Mr Peynado</persName> &amp; that he\n                                        would<lb/> likewise furnish me with one, but I am now near\n                                        the close<lb/> of the second day and have not yet heard from\n                                        him and think<lb/> it probable that he may feel too\n                                        indifferent, to give himself the<lb/> trouble.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><persName>Mr Isaac's</persName> apology was\n                                        sufficiently lame &amp; not at all<lb/> in the <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">terms</hi> in which he expressed\n                                        himself to me on the subject<lb/> but it was at least an\n                                        apology; doing you justice if not<lb/> himself</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have nothing of moment to add. All are well<lb/>\n                                        and desire regards.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(9)\">Yours truly</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(11)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">E. Block</persName>\n                              </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3j679g91/canvas/p2"
